<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About • Notion</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.8/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-sRIl4kxILFvY47J16cr9ZwB07vP4J8+LH7qKQnuqkuIAvNWLzeN8tE5YBujZqJLB" crossorigin="anonymous">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header class="d-flex flex-wrap justify-content-center py-3 mb-4 border-bottom">
            <a href="/" class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3 mb-md-0 me-md-auto link-body-emphasis text-decoration-none">
                <svg class="bi me-2" width="40" height="32" aria-hidden="true">
                    <use xlink:href="#bootstrap"></use>
                </svg>
                <span class="fs-4">Main Menu</span>
            </a>
            <ul class="nav nav-pills">
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="/" class="nav-link" aria-current="page">My Notes</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="/add" class="nav-link">Add</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="/about" class="nav-link active">About</a></li>
            </ul>
        </header>
    </div>

    <main class="container mb-5">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-8">

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h1 class="h3 mb-3">About this project</h1>
                    <p class="lead">
                        This website is a small personal project for keeping track of thoughts and notes about books using their ISBNs.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        For each note, you provide the book’s ISBN and your own text, and the main page shows your notes together with the book covers so you can quickly see what you have been reading.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can edit or delete any of your notes at any time, so your collection stays clean and up to date as your opinions change or you finish new books.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">How it works</h2>
                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            Add a new note by entering the book’s ISBN and your comments about it.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            The app uses the ISBN to fetch and display the corresponding book cover on the main page.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            From the main page, you can open, edit, or delete any note you have created before.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-4">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Tech stack</h2>
                    <p>
                        This app is built with <strong>Node.js</strong> and <strong>Express.js</strong> on the backend, using <strong>EJS</strong> templates to render server-side HTML.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The interface is styled with <strong>Bootstrap 5</strong> for a simple, responsive layout without much custom CSS.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Why ISBN?</h2>
                    <p>
                        The International Standard Book Number (ISBN) uniquely identifies each book edition, which makes it a reliable way to attach the right cover and details to your notes.
                    </p>
                </section>

            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.8/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-Iu7rLq71lJZIe0xOrE7wBtOxfMhJzT2CPYqvZ1qLwoCydK4sqGJcGf7Sx0QK8z+4" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</body>
</html>

